instruct jurors to disregard Joyce's comment instead of declaring a 
mistrial, but he also apologized. 
</P>
<P>
	``There was never an intent to convict Captain Ashby because he  
exercised his constitutional right, which we are sworn to defend,'' 
Daugherty said. 
</P>
<P>
	If convicted of both obstruction of justice and conspiracy,  
Ashby could be dismissed from the Marines or sentenced to up to 10 
years in prison. Last month, he was acquitted of involuntary 
manslaughter charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Ashby has admitted he gave the videotape to his navigator, Capt.  
