prosecutors the option of granting immunity to Schweitzer for his 
testimony in Ashby's trial. Schweitzer already has pleaded guilty 
to the same charges Ashby now faces. Keller also ruled Schweitzer 
may invoke his 5th Amendment right against self-incrimination at 
any time. 
