<HEADLINE> Missing Mother Found in Texas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- A mother who disappeared after her two  
young children were found dead in a creek last week was picked up 
by police in a Corpus Christi apartment Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tina Marie Cornelius, 22, was taken in for questioning, although  
she has not been arrested. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers were investigating a claim by a man who said Ms.  
Cornelius told him a day before the bodies were found that their 
father had taken the children and that they had died by falling off 
a cliff. 
</P>
<P>
	``She is alive and well,'' said Texas Department of Public  
Safety Officer Mike Cox. ``She has no apparent injuries.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies of Ms. Cornelius' children, 3-year-old Amanda Lee  
Miller and 2-year-old Dominick Logan Cornelius, were found April 19 
in six inches of water in Brushy Creek near Hutto, about 20 miles 
north of Austin. 
</P>
<P>
	Amanda died of suffocation and her brother died from a cracked  
skull. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities had since searched for the mother, saying they  
feared she might have met with foul play. Police said then that the 
mother was not considered a suspect. 
</P>
<P>
	The children were last seen April 14 when Ms. Cornelius -- who  
worked as a topless dancer -- picked them up from day care, 
according to police. They were found five days later, but police do 
not believe they had been there long. 
</P>
</TEXT>
