<HEADLINE> Kings' Courtnall Undergoes Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Los Angeles Kings right wing Russ  
Courtnall underwent arthroscopic surgery on his left shoulder 
Wednesday to repair a partially torn tendon and remove scar tissue 
in his rotator cuff. 
</P>
<P>
	Kings team physician Dr. Ronald Kvitne of the Kerlan-Jobe  
Orthopaedic Clinic performed the operation. The Kings said 
Courtnall would begin rehabilitation immediately and a full 
recovery is expected. 
</P>
<P>
	Courtnall, 33, played in 57 games for the Kings this season and  
had six goals and 13 assists. In 1,019 career NHL games, he has 297 
goals and 447 assists. 
</P>
