<HEADLINE> Indians Put Shuey on 15-Day DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Right-handed reliever Paul Shuey was put  
on the 15-day disabled list Wednesday by the Cleveland Indians 
because of a strained left hamstring and was replaced by 
right-hander Paul Wagner. 
</P>
<P>
	Shuey, who is 2-1 with a 2.13 ERA in a team-high 11 appearances  
this season, hurt his leg throwing a pitch in the eighth inning of 
the Indians' game at Boston on Sunday. He was placed on the DL 
retroactive to Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Shuey, who has held hitters to a .188 average this season, is on  
the disabled list for the seventh time in five seasons in the 
majors. He twice before has been sidelined with hamstring problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner's contract was purchased from Buffalo of the Triple-A  
International League. He was 1-0 with a 1.04 ERA in three starts 
for Buffalo. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room on the 40-man roster for Wagner, the Indians  
transferred left-handed pitcher Tom Martin, who is recovering from 
shoulder surgery, from the 15-day disabled list to the 60-day 
disabled list. 
</P>
