<HEADLINE> Crew 1, Wizards 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Jason Farrell's goal in the 88th minute  
Wednesday gave the Columbus Crew a 1-0 victory over the winless 
Kansas City Wizards. 
</P>
<P>
	Kansas City (0-7), playing its final game under interim coach  
Ken Fogerty, suffered its fifth shutout loss of the season and the 
eighth in a 10-game losing streak dating back to last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the game, former U.S. national team coach Bob Gansler was  
named Kansas City's new head coach. He takes over on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Columbus (4-2) managed just six shots in the game. But the Crew  
avoided a shootout when Farrell slipped past the Kansas City 
defense to take a long pass from Andy Williams, then took one step 
and fired a shot past goalkeeper Chris Snitko from 10 yards out. 
</P>
<P>
	Matt Kmosko was credited with an assist on the play.  
</P>
</TEXT>
