<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Heat's Mourning Out 2 More Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Miami Heat center Alonzo Mourning will miss at  
least two more games after being diagnosed Wednesday with a slight 
fracture of his right eye socket. 
</P>
<P>
	Surgery won't be necessary, but Miami's leading scorer and  
rebounder will have to wear a protective device in the playoffs for 
the second consecutive season. 
</P>
<P>
	``Whether it's a face mask or goggles, we won't know until after  
he tries some things on,'' team spokesman Tim Donovan said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mourning missed two games last season and played with a  
protective mask for 10 more after breaking his left cheekbone in a 
late-season collision against Boston. 
</P>
<P>
	Mourning, who missed Tuesday night's win at New Jersey, will sit  
out games Thursday against Boston and Saturday against Chicago but 
could be back Sunday at home against Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
	Mourning is having perhaps his best season, averaging 20.3  
points and 11.0 rebounds and leading the league in blocked shots 
with a 4.0 average. He was considered a strong candidate for league 
MVP. 
</P>
<P>
	His latest injury came in the first quarter of Monday night's  
90-65 win at Cleveland, when the Cavaliers' Cedric Henderson hit 
him in the face. 
</P>
<P>
	Mourning continued playing, finishing with 23 points, 12  
rebounds and four blocks. But he complained of discomfort afterward 
and was sent home Tuesday for further examination, missing that 
night's win at New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	A second facial injury to Mourning caused coach Pat Riley to say  
that officials need to pay closer attention to what defenders are 
doing to his star center. 
</P>
<P>
	``This guy gets pounded and hit in the head more than any player  
I have ever coached in my life -- over the head, in the face,'' 
Riley said. ``He's just fortunate he doesn't get hurt more.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
