<DOCNO> APW19990428.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-28 10:25:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	
</P>
<P>
	In the spotlight: Randy Travis  
</P>
<P>
	 *Personal stats:* Randy Bruce Traywick was born on May 4, 1959,  
in Marshville, N.C. He began singing country music and playing 
guitar at 8. He moved to Charlotte, N.C., at 16 and performed in 
nightclubs for five years. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 1970s, he stacked up arrests and spent numerous weekends  
in a county jail in Monroe, N.C. But after winning a talent contest 
at Country City USA in Charlotte in 1977 -- and pairing with manager 
Lib Hatcher, now his wife, -- he managed to break into big-time 
country music as Randy Travis. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd come from a house where some crazy things went on. My  
father was a little bit wild and still is. I didn't know anything 
else. It was just the way we lived,'' he has said. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Making music:* In the 1980s, his hits like ``On the Other  
Hand'' and ``Forever and Ever, Amen'' steered country music back to 
its traditional roots, and arguably to the sales boom of the early 
1990s. 
</P>
<P>
	``Storms of Life'' appeared in mid-1986. It went platinum in  
less than a year. His next two albums, ``Always and Forever'' and 
``8 X 10,'' won Grammy Awards. 
</P>
<P>
	``This Is Me'' and ``Before You Kill Us All'' kept him in the  
top 10 in 1994. ``Whisper My Name'' became his 19th No. 1 hit that 
same year. In 1995 he hit the top 10 with ``The Box.'' 
</P>
<P>
	 *Making films:* Travis has appeared in several films including  
``Young Guns,'' ``Frank and Jesse,'' ``Fire Down Below,'' ``The 
Rainmaker'' and ``Baby Geniuses.'' His upcoming films include 
``White River Kid'' with Antonio Banderas and Ellen Barkin. 
</P>
<P>
	 *Quote:* ``I still want to compete! I want to be out there and  
getting the airplay and selling tickets and playing shows. I don't 
want to quit. I love this. That's what it boils down to, I love to 
sing. You have to want to do it and continue putting out quality 
material.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays for May 2-8:  
</P>
<P>
	May 2: Actor Roscoe Lee Browne is 74. Singer Lesley Gore is 53.  
Singer Lou Gramm of Foreigner is 49. Actress Christine Baranski is 
47. Actress Jenna Von Oy (``Blossom'') is 22. 
</P>
<P>
	May 3: Folk singer Pete Seeger is 80. Singer James Brown is 66.  
Singer Engelbert Humperdinck is 63. Singer Frankie Valli is 62. 
Singer Christopher Cross is 48. 
</P>
<P>
	May 4: Singer Jackie Jackson of The Jacksons is 48. Country  
singer Randy Travis is 40. Actress Mary McDonough (``The Waltons'') 
is 38. Musician Mike Dirnt of Green Day is 27. Musician Jose 
Castellanos of Save Ferris is 22. Singer Lance Bass of 'N Sync is 
20. 
</P>
<P>
	May 5: Actress Ann B. Davis (``The Brady Bunch'') is 73. Actor  
Michael Murphy is 61. Comedian-actor Michael Palin is 56. Singer 
Ian McCullough of Echo and the Bunnymen is 40. Actress Tina Yothers 
(``Family Ties'') is 26. Actress Danielle Fishel (``Boy Meets 
World'') is 18. 
</P>
<P>
	May 6: Singer Bob Seger is 54. Actor George Clooney is 38.  
Actress Roma Downey is 36. Musician Mark Bryan of Hootie and the 
Blowfish is 32. 
</P>
<P>
	May 7: Musician Phil Campbell of Motorhead is 38.  
Singer-musician Chris O'Connor of Primitive Radio Gods is 34. 
Actress Traci Lords is 30. 
</P>
<P>
	May 8: Comedian Don Rickles is 73. Singer Toni Tennille is 56.  
Musician Chris Frantz of Talking Heads is 48. Actor David Keith is 
45. Musician Alex Van Halen of Van Halen is 44. Actress Melissa 
Gilbert is 35. Musician Dave Rowntree of Blur is 35. 
</P>
