<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Asian Stock Markets Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HONG KONG (AP) -- Most Asian markets fell Wednesday, despite an  
overnight rise on Wall Street, with sentiment turning negative on 
the region's top exchanges, Tokyo and Hong Kong. 
</P>
<P>
	Tokyo prices fell slightly as some investors sold shares before  
a series of national holidays, while the U.S. dollar slipped 
against the yen. 
</P>
<P>
	The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average lost 15.03 points,  
or 0.09 percent, ending the day at 16,942.24. On Tuesday, the 
Nikkei had risen 0.23 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar bought 119.08 yen at late afternoon, down 0.38 yen  
from late Tuesday in Tokyo but below its late New York level of 
120.40 yen overnight. The currency ranged from 118.25 yen to 120.28 
yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Tokyo shares rose early in the session, following Wall Street's  
latest gains, but slipped in later dealings. 
</P>
<P>
	``Demand was quite strong in the morning after shares in New  
York rose overnight, but sell orders began after the Nikkei average 
surpassed the 17,000 mark,'' said Yoshio Watanabe of Toyo 
Securities in Tokyo. 
</P>
<P>
	In Hong Kong, blue chips fell 1.7 percent as investor sentiment  
turned negative. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hang Seng Index dropped 231.40 points to close at 13,133.39.  
On Tuesday, the index gained 237.77 points, adding to powerful 
recent gains. 
</P>
<P>
	``As the index spilled downward, some investors joined the  
sell-off bandwagon, triggering a greater level of loss,'' said 
George Chan of Celestial Asia Securities Holdings Ltd. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecommunications shares, which had fueled the market's recent  
rally, fell on widespread negative sentiment, dragging the utility 
issues down 3.6 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	ELSEWHERE:   	
</P>
<P>
	BANGKOK: Shares fell following other regional markets. The SET  
index fell 2.11 points, or 0.49 percent, to close at 423.22. 
</P>
<P>
	JAKARTA: Shares rose on foreign buying in selected blue chips.  
The JSX Composite Index rose 12.139 points, or 2.6 percent, to 
close at 481.344. 
</P>
<P>
	KUALA LUMPUR: Shares fell on a correction following a recent  
bull run. The Kuala Lumpur Composite Index fell 8.39 points, or 1.3 
percent, to close at 661.63. 
</P>
<P>
	MANILA: Shares rose on Wall Street's overnight gains and recent  
interest rate cuts. The PSE Index rose 39.14 points, or 1.6 
percent, to close at 2,459.99. 
</P>
<P>
	TAIPEI: Shares fell amid concern that first-quarter earnings  
might be worse than expected. The Weighted Price Index fell 53.52 
points, or 0.70 percent, to 7,496.61. 
</P>
<P>
	SINGAPORE: Shares fell on a sudden market correction in the  
afternoon. The STI fell 39.23 points, or 2.1 percent, to close at 
1,837.16. 
</P>
<P>
	SYDNEY: Shares fell as unexpected inflation figures dashed hopes  
for an interest rate cut. The All Ordinaries Index was down 22.5 
points, or 0.72 percent, to close at 3,122.7. 
</P>
<P>
	WELLINGTON: Shares rose on gains in Air New Zealand Ltd. and  
Carter Holt Harvey Ltd. The NZSE-40 was up 7.24 points, or 0.31 
percent, to close at 2,278.31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
