<HEADLINE> Exhumations in Hospital Death Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GLENDALE, Calif. (AP) -- Twenty bodies will be exhumed as part of  
an investigation of a respiratory therapist who last year claimed 
to have killed dozens of terminally ill patients at a suburban 
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators will begin examining bodies this week, police  
Chief Russell Siverling said Wednesday. Permission from the 
families wasn't needed, and Siverling wouldn't say whether any 
families objected. 
</P>
