	Efren Saldivar, 28, told police he killed up to 50 Glendale  
Adventist Medical Center patients he believed were terminally ill. 
Saldivar, who called himself an ``angel of death,'' later recanted, 
saying he was suicidal and wanted to be sentenced to death row. 
</P>
<P>
	Saldivar and four hospital colleagues were fired, but no  
criminal charges have been filed. 
</P>
