<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Osmonds To Host Beauty Pageant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- There they are: new Miss America hosts Donny  
and Marie Osmond. 
</P>
<P>
	The brother and sister act will replace last year's hosts,  
Boomer Esiason and Meredith Vieira, pageant officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Osmonds, popular TV and concert performers in the '70s and  
'80s, reunited last fall for a syndicated talk show. 
</P>
<P>
	The pageant has had a rapid turnover of hosts following Bert  
Parks' quarter-century reign, which ended in 1980. Parks was best 
known for serenading Miss America winners with the trademark 
anthem, ``There She Is.'' He died of lung cancer in 1992 at age 77. 
</P>
<P>
	The 79th annual Miss America Pageant, dubbed Miss America 2000,  
will be broadcast live from Atlantic City, N.J., on ABC on Sept. 
18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
