<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Scotland Upsets Germany in Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Scotland beat Germany for the first time in 40 years, getting a  
66th-minute goal from Don Hutchison in a 1-0 victory in an 
exhibition game Wednesday night at Bremen. 
</P>
<P>
	Scotland had been winless in six games against the Germans since  
1959. 
</P>
<P>
	At Arnhem, Youssef Chippo scored in the 59th minute and  
Salaheddine Bassir scored 10 minutes later as Morocco beat the 
Netherlands 2-1 in another exhibition game. 
</P>
<P>
	African player of the year Mustafa Hadji set up both goals. Ruud  
van Nistelrooij scored in the final minute for the Dutch. 
</P>
<P>
	Italy played a scoreless tie against Serbia at Zagreb, and  
England conceded its first goal against Hungary in seven games 
since 1981 in a 1-1 tie at Budapest. 
</P>
<P>
	With England missing 14 regulars because of injury, Alan Shearer  
put the visitors ahead with a penalty kick in the 21st minute. But 
Janos Hrutka tied the score on a 25-yard free kick with 13 minutes 
to go. 
</P>
<P>
	At Dublin, Ireland ended Sweden's nine-game unbeaten streak,  
winning 2-0 on goals by Graham Kavanagh in the 75th minute and Mark 
Kennedy in the 77th. Kavanaugh was playing his first international 
game. 
</P>
<P>
	In European Championship qualifiers, Norway (3-1-1) won 4-1 at  
Georgia (1-3-1) and took over the Group Two lead. Tore Andre Flo 
scored twice, and Steffen Iversen and Ole Gunnar Solskjaer got one 
goal each -- all in the first 34 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Albania (0-1-3) and Latvia (2-1-2) tied 0-0 in the same group  
while Austria (3-1-1), a 9-0 loser against Spain a month ago, took 
over the Group Six lead with a 7-0 rout over San Marino (0-6) at 
Graz. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
