<HEADLINE> Report: Bayer Plans Plant Closings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) -- German drug and chemical giant Bayer  
plans to save about $382 million by closing four or five 
pharmaceutical plants worldwide over the next three years, a 
business weekly reported Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The cuts will include German and other European operations,  
company chairman Manfred Schneider was quoted as saying by the 
publication Wirtschaftswoche. In Germany, Bayer's pharmaceutical 
businesses will be merged, the story said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bayer officials were not immediately available for comment.  
</P>
<P>
	Schneider also said Bayer plans to build a second biotechnology  
plant, probably in Germany, according to the report. 
</P>
<P>
	Bayer releases first-quarter data Friday. Analysts expect a drop  
in earnings after Bayer revealed a 10 percent fall in combined 
January and February sales. 
</P>
