<HEADLINE> Pitcher Charged After Beaning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- A University of Evansville baseball  
player who was hit in the face by a pitch as he stood about 15 feet 
from home plate has charged the Wichita State pitcher who hit him 
with assault. 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony Molina, who had fractures of three bones around his left  
eye, said Ben Christensen hit him intentionally while warming up 
before Friday's game. 
</P>
<P>
	Molina filed assault charges with Wichita police.  
</P>
<P>
	``My main concern right now is about seeing again,'' Molina  
said. ``They told me today that my vision is 20/400 in my left eye, 
and that there's a chance I might never get my vision all the way 
back. 
</P>
<P>
	Christensen was quoted in the Wichita State Eagle as saying that  
he threw toward Molina to keep him from timing pitches while on 
deck, but that he never intended to hit him. 
</P>
<P>
	The Missouri Valley Conference is investigating.  
</P>
</TEXT>
