<HEADLINE> Burnham in As Raytheon Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Mass. (AP) -- Raytheon president and CEO Daniel  
Burnham will assume the additional role of chairman of the board of 
directors, replacing Dennis Picard. 
</P>
<P>
	Picard, 66, stepped down as CEO in December. On Wednesday,  
Raytheon said said he would retire as chairman on July 31. He will 
continue to serve on the board. 
</P>
<P>
	Picard has worked at Raytheon for 44 years, and became chairman  
and chief executive officer in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
	Burnham, 52, joined Raytheon in July 1998. Picard called  
Burnham, ``the right man at the right time'' to lead the company. 
</P>
<P>
	Raytheon sells products and services for commercial and defense  
electronics, engineering and construction. 
</P>
