<HEADLINE> Renault To Build Plant in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- French automaker Renault on Wednesday  
laid the cornerstone of a $120 million engine plant in southern 
Brazil. 
</P>
<P>
	The new factory will be built in the city of Curitiba, 217 miles  
southwest of Sao Paulo, next to the auto plant Renault inaugurated 
less than a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	The plant is expected to be concluded by early 2000 with an  
initial annual output of 57,000 engines, the automaker's press 
office said. By 2002, the factory will be producing 280,000 units a 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	The engines to be produced at the new plant will equip the cars  
produced by Renault in Brazil and Argentina and will later be 
exported to other Latin American countries. 
</P>
<P>
	They will also equip the cars that will be made by Peugeot,  
which is building a factory in the state of Rio de Janeiro. Peugeot 
is expected to purchase 250,000 Renault engines between 2001 and 
2005. 
</P>
<P>
	Inaugurated Dec.4, 1998 the Renault factory produces the Scenic  
minivan and will start making the Clio compact model later this 
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
