<HEADLINE> Dollar, Gold Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar fell against other major currencies in  
European trading Wednesday. Gold also rose. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0662, up from $1.0633 Tuesday. The  
British pound was quoted at $1.6170, up from $1.6158. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was quoted at 118.86 Japanese yen, down from 120.15.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the euro was at $1.0620 and the  
pound was at $1.6138. The dollar bought 119.24 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Tuesday: 1.5078 Swiss  
francs, down from 1.5090; and 1.4759 Canadian dollars, down from 
1.4818. 
</P>
